-- DP World Aims to Have 80% Financing From Long-Term Instruments, CFO Says
-- B y   A r i f   S h a r i f
-- 2010-10-13T10:45:01Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-13/dp-world-aims-to-have-80-financing-from-long-term-instruments-cfo-says.html
DP World Ltd., the port operator
owned by debt-laden Dubai World, aims to have 80 percent
financing from long-term instruments, Chief Financial Officer
Yuvraj Narayan said at a conference in Dubai today.  DP World’s requirements for working capital are “light,”
he said. Long-term financing usually refers to five years or
more.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Arif Sharif in Dubai at 
